corpus = []
#with open('paper_filtered_2018.jl') as f:
with open('paper_filtered_10yr.jl') as f: 
    for line in f:
        corpus.append(json.loads(line))

# Clean up the data and remove:
# leading and trailing white space
# replace end of line symbol '\n' with white sapce
for document in corpus:
    document['BODY'] = document['paperAbstract'].strip().replace('\n',' ')

# Put corpus into dataframe
data = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(corpus)

#####################################
## Generate Topics with NMF over TF-IDF 
#####################################

NVM_FEATURES = 1000
NVM_TOPICS = 10
NVM_TOP_WORDS = 10


def print_top_words(model, feature_names, n_top_words):
    for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(model.components_):
        print("\nTopic #%d:" % topic_idx)
        print(" ".join([feature_names[i]
                        for i in topic.argsort()[:-n_top_words - 1:-1]]))
    print()


tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_df=0.75, min_df=2,max_features=NVM_FEATURES,stop_words='english')
tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(data['BODY'])
nmf = NMF(n_components=NVM_TOPICS, random_state=0,alpha=.1, l1_ratio=.5).fit(tfidf)

print("Topics found via NMF:")
tfidf_feature_names = tfidf_vectorizer.get_feature_names()
print_top_words(nmf, tfidf_feature_names, NVM_TOP_WORDS)

## Examine the Most Represetative Paper of Each Topic

nmf_embedding = nmf.transform(tfidf)
top_idx = np.argsort(nmf_embedding,axis=0)[-3:]
count = 0
for idxs in top_idx.T: 
    print("\nTopic {}:".format(count))
    for idx in idxs:
        print(data.iloc[idx]['title'])
    count += 1

#####################################
## Plot the Topic Distribution of Each Year from 2009 - 2018 
#####################################

matplotlib.rc('font',family='monospace')
plt.style.use('ggplot')

fig, axs = plt.subplots(5,2, figsize=(10, 15), facecolor='w', edgecolor='k')
fig.subplots_adjust(hspace = .1, wspace=0)
axs = axs.ravel()
count = 0
legend = []

for year, idx in zip([2009,2010,2011,2012,2013,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018], range(10)):
    plot_data = tsne_embedding[data['year']==year]
    scatter = axs[idx].scatter(data=plot_data,x='x',y='y',s=2,c=plot_data['hue'],cmap="Set1")
    axs[idx].set_title('published in {}'.format(year),**{'fontsize':'10'})
    axs[idx].axis('off')

plt.suptitle("Natural Language Processing Research Trends by Topic",**{'fontsize':'14','weight':'bold'})
plt.figtext(.51,0.95,'topic modelling with NMF over TF-IDF based on paper abstract and T-SNE visualization', **{'fontsize':'10','weight':'light'}, ha='center')

fig.legend(legend_list,topics,loc=(0.02,0.89),ncol=4)
plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.85)
plt.show()
